Subject: Proposal for Improved Process on MTE Oracle Database Ticket Resolution

Hi [Recipient's Name],

I hope this message finds you well.

I would like to address an ongoing issue we’ve encountered with the current process for password resets and account unlocks in the MTE Oracle database. As you may be aware, when we raise tickets for these requests, they are often closed without any confirmation that the issue has been resolved.

Currently, there seems to be a lack of communication between the requestor and the person resolving the ticket. Updates are being made directly in MTE, stating that the request has been sent to the application owner, but there is no email communication or Teams chat to confirm that the issue has been addressed.

I believe this process needs to be improved for the following reasons:

Accountability: It is crucial that the application owner is involved as an approver during the request process.
User Confirmation: The final password reset or account unlock should always be communicated directly to the requestor. This ensures that the user is informed and can verify that their issue has been resolved.
Enhanced Communication: Before closing any ticket, the responsible team should check in with the user to confirm resolution.
Implementing these changes will not only streamline the process but also enhance user satisfaction and accountability.

Thank you for considering this proposal. I am looking forward to your thoughts on how we can improve this process.

Best regards,

[Your Name]
[Your Position]
[Your Contact Information]
[Your Company]




